B. Articular fossa: This is part of the temporal bone where the lower jaw articulates. It's located on the lateral aspect of the skull, near the temple.

C. Carotid canal: This is a passage in the temporal bone through which the internal carotid artery passes. It's located near the base of the skull, close to the jugular foramen.

D. Foramen lacerum: This is a perforated area in the base of the skull where several nerves and blood vessels pass. It's located between the sphenoid and temporal bones.
